Hot and Sour Soup

1" ginger, grated 
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 can bambook stalks, sliced
6 dried black fungus, soaked and sliced
6 dried shiitake mushrooms, soaked and sliced
1 block tofu, cubed
2 tbsp chili garlic sauce
2 tbsp oil
1/4 c soy sauce
1/4 c rice wine vinegar
3 tbsp cornstarch + 1/4 c water
2 quarts chinese chicken stock
1 egg, beaten
pinch of pepper
pinch of sugar
scallions (garnish)
cilantro (garnish)

Soak the dried fungus in boiling water for ~ 20 min. Heat oil in a large, heavy pot over medium heat. Add the garlic, ginger, and chili garlic sauce. Let this cook until it's fragrant, ~ 3min. Do not let the garlic or ginger burn. Add the bamboo and mushrooms, stir to combine. Add soy sauce and rice wine vinegar. Add chicken stock and bring soup to a simmer. Make a slurry with the cornstarch + water; slowly add the slurry to the soup. Once combined, add the tofu. Let simmer for a few minutes, then add pinch of pepper and sugar. Beat the egg and drizzle into the pot. Serve with chopped cilantro and scallions.

Chinese Chicken Stock

1 chicken carcass
2 " ginger, cut into coins
6 cloves garlic, halved
6 scallions
1 medium onion, quartered
20 black peppercorns
5-6 dried red chilies
3 quarts water

place all ingredients in a stock pot, bring to boil, reduce the heat and simmer for 3 hrs. Let the stock cool, then strain the solids.
